# Pinned clang-tidy major version: 19 (matches .clang-format, spec/commit.md #4).
#
# Modest starter set for the CUDA/C++ kernel code that lands in commit 10+
# (cuda/csrc/): bugprone-*, performance-*, readability-* minus the noisy
# naming/magic-number checks that fight kernel-code conventions (short index
# names like `i`/`j`/`tid`, numeric literals in tuning code).
#
# This check set only fully activates once `compile_commands.json` exists
# (commit 10, `cuda/` scaffold + kernel-builder); until then there are no
# .cu/.cpp/.h/.hpp files for it to run against.
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  readability-*,
  -readability-identifier-naming,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -readability-magic-numbers

WarningsAsErrors: ''
HeaderFilterRegex: '.*'
FormatStyle: file
